---
description: Enforce persistent repo brain workflow
alwaysApply: true
---

Before making any meaningful change, review:
- brain/project_context.md
- brain/current_state.md
- brain/decisions.md
- brain/next_steps.md

When planning or implementing work:
- align changes with the documented project context
- preserve existing architecture unless intentionally changing it
- note assumptions when context is missing
- avoid blind edits without first understanding affected modules

After any meaningful change:
- update brain/current_state.md
- append an entry to brain/change_log.md
- update brain/next_steps.md
- add a decision entry to brain/decisions.md if an architectural, tooling, or workflow choice was made

If brain files do not exist, create them.
Do not finish work without leaving the repo in a resumable state.
